	<a name="footnote22-00785_002_039">22.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">El presidente Spencer W. Kimball dijo: &ldquo;&hellip;existe una impresi&oacute;n imperante, quiz&aacute;s subconsciente, de que el Se&ntilde;or dispuso el arrepentimiento &uacute;nicamente para aquellos que cometan homicidio o adulterio o hurto u otros cr&iacute;menes atroces. Eso, por supuesto, no es verdad. Si somos humildes y sentimos deseos de obedecer el Evangelio, llegaremos a considerar el arrepentimiento como algo que se aplica a todo lo que hagamos en la vida, bien sea de naturaleza espiritual o temporal. El arrepentimiento es para toda alma que a&uacute;n no haya llegado a la perfecci&oacute;n&rdquo; (<span class="emphasis">Ense&ntilde;anzas de los Presidentes de la Iglesia: Spencer W. Kimball, </span>p&aacute;g. 41). V&eacute;ase tambi&eacute;n <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/1-jn/1.8?lang=spa#7" target="_blank">1 Juan 1:8</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/4.29-30?lang=spa#28" target="_blank">Mos&iacute;ah 4:29&ndash;30</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote23-00785_002_039"><a name="-00785_002_039">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote23-00785_002_039">23.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/68.25?lang=spa#24" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 68:25</a>; cursiva agregada.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote24-00785_002_039"><a name="-00785_002_039">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote24-00785_002_039">24.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">El vocablo metanoeo,<sup> </sup><span class="emphasis">&mu;&epsilon;&tau;&alpha;&nu;&omicron;&epsilon;&omega;,</span> se us&oacute; en el texto griego de las declaraciones del Se&ntilde;or que se encuentran en <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/4.17?lang=spa#16" target="_blank">Mateo 4:17</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/mark/1.15?lang=spa#14" target="_blank">Marcos 1:15</a> y <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/luke/13.3?lang=spa#2" target="_blank">Lucas 13:3</a>. Pedro us&oacute; el mismo vocablo en <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/acts/2.38?lang=spa#37" target="_blank">Hechos 2:38</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/acts/3.19?lang=spa#18" target="_blank">Hechos 3:19</a>; y <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/acts/8.22?lang=spa#21" target="_blank">Hechos 8:22</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote25-00785_002_039"><a name="-00785_002_039">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote25-00785_002_039">25.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">En <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/17.2?lang=spa#1" target="_blank">Mateo 17:2</a> y <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/mark/9.2?lang=spa#1" target="_blank">Marcos 9:2</a>, la palabra <span class="emphasis">transfigur&oacute;</span> se tradujo del vocablo <span class="emphasis">metamorphoo</span>, que significa &ldquo;cambio de forma&rdquo;.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote26-00785_002_039"><a name="-00785_002_039">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote26-00785_002_039">26.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">En <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/eph/4.23?lang=spa#22" target="_blank">Efesios 4:23</a>, el vocablo <span class="emphasis">mente</span> se tradujo de la palabra griega <span class="emphasis">nous</span>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote27-00785_002_039"><a name="-00785_002_039">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote27-00785_002_039">27.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">En <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/luke/1.77?lang=spa#76" target="_blank">Lucas 1:77</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/rom/2.20?lang=spa#19" target="_blank">Romanos 2:20</a>; y <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/2-cor/6.6?lang=spa#5" target="_blank">2 Corintios 6:6</a>, las palabras <span class="emphasis">conocimiento </span>y<span class="emphasis"> ciencia </span>se tradujeron del vocablo <span class="emphasis">gnos</span> o <span class="emphasis">gnosis</span>. <span class="emphasis">Gnos</span>, cuando es precedido por el prefijo negativo <span class="emphasis">a-,</span> significa &ldquo;falta de conocimiento&rdquo;, como en la palabra <span class="emphasis">agnostic </span>[agn&oacute;stico]. En <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/acts/17.23?lang=spa#22" target="_blank">Hechos 17:23</a> la palabra <span class="emphasis">desconocido</span> se tradujo del vocablo <span class="emphasis">agnostos, </span>y las palabras <span class="emphasis">sin</span> <span class="emphasis">conocerle</span> se tradujeron del vocablo <span class="emphasis">agnoeo</span>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote28-00785_002_039"><a name="-00785_002_039">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote28-00785_002_039">28.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">En <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/12.18?lang=spa#17" target="_blank">Mateo 12:18</a> y <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/rom/8.5?lang=spa#4" target="_blank">Romanos 8:5</a>, la palabra <span class="emphasis">Esp&iacute;ritu</span> se tradujo del vocablo griego <span class="emphasis">pneuma</span>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote29-00785_002_039"><a name="-00785_002_039">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote29-00785_002_039">29.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">En <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/acts/17.25?lang=spa#24" target="_blank">Hechos 17:25</a>, la palabra <span class="emphasis">aliento</span> se tradujo del vocablo griego <span class="emphasis">pnoe</span>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote30-00785_002_039"><a name="-00785_002_039">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote30-00785_002_039">30.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/2.21?lang=spa#20" target="_blank">Mos&iacute;ah 2:21</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote31-00785_002_039"><a name="-00785_002_039">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote31-00785_002_039">31.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/27.21,27?lang=spa#20" target="_blank">3 Nefi 27:21, 27</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote32-00785_002_039"><a name="-00785_002_039">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote32-00785_002_039">32.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/37.35-36?lang=spa#34" target="_blank">Alma 37:35&ndash;36</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote33-00785_002_039"><a name="-00785_002_039">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote33-00785_002_039">33.</a>
      </span>
				<p class=""><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/5.14?lang=spa#13" target="_blank">Alma 5:14</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote34-00785_002_039"><a name="-00785_002_039">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote34-00785_002_039">34.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/john/3.3,7?lang=spa#2" target="_blank">Juan 3:3, 7</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/27.25?lang=spa#24" target="_blank">Mos&iacute;ah 27:25</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/5.49?lang=spa#48" target="_blank">Alma 5:49</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/7.14?lang=spa#13" target="_blank">Alma 7:14</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.59?lang=spa#58" target="_blank">Mois&eacute;s 6:59</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote35-00785_002_039"><a name="-00785_002_039">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote35-00785_002_039">35.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/moro/10.32?lang=spa#31" target="_blank">Moroni 10:32</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote36-00785_002_039"><a name="-00785_002_039">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote36-00785_002_039">36.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/gal/6.7-8?lang=spa#6" target="_blank">G&aacute;latas 6:7&ndash;8</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote37-00785_002_039"><a name="-00785_002_039">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote37-00785_002_039">37.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/judg/13.7?lang=spa#6" target="_blank">Jueces 13:7</a>; <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/luke/1.15?lang=spa#14" target="_blank">Lucas 1:15</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/89.5,7-9?lang=spa#4" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 89:5, 7–9</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote38-00785_002_039"><a name="-00785_002_039">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote38-00785_002_039">38.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/5.27-28?lang=spa#26" target="_blank">Mateo 5:27&ndash;28</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/38.12?lang=spa#11" target="_blank">Alma 38:12</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/12.27-28?lang=spa#26" target="_blank">3 Nefi 12:27&ndash;28</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/42.23?lang=spa#22" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 42:23</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote39-00785_002_039"><a name="-00785_002_039">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote39-00785_002_039">39.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/rom/8.5-6?lang=spa#4" target="_blank">Romanos 8:5&ndash;6</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote40-00785_002_039"><a name="-00785_002_039">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote40-00785_002_039">40.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/38.11?lang=spa#10" target="_blank">Alma 38:11</a>; <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/121.37?lang=spa#36" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 121:37</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote41-00785_002_039"><a name="-00785_002_039">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote41-00785_002_039">41.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/john/13.15?lang=spa#14" target="_blank">Juan 13:15</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/1-tim/4.12?lang=spa#11" target="_blank">1 Timoteo 4:12</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/1-pet/2.21?lang=spa#20" target="_blank">1 Pedro 2:21</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/31.16?lang=spa#15" target="_blank">2 Nefi 31:16</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/18.16?lang=spa#15" target="_blank">3 Nefi 18:16</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/morm/7.10?lang=spa#9" target="_blank">Morm&oacute;n 7:10</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote42-00785_002_039"><a name="-00785_002_039">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote42-00785_002_039">42.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="https://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/121.45?lang=spa#44" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 121:45</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote43-00785_002_039"><a name="-00785_002_039">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote43-00785_002_039">43.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/85.3?lang=spa#2" target="_blank">Doctrina y Convenios 85:3</a>.</p>
			</li><li class="footnote " id="footnote44-00785_002_039"><a name="-00785_002_039">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote44-00785_002_039">44.</a>
      </span>
				<p class="">V&eacute;ase <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/philip/4.8?lang=spa#7" target="_blank">Filipenses 4:8</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/pgp/a-of-f/1.13?lang=spa#12" target="_blank">Art&iacute;culos de Fe 1:13</a>.</p>
